Document: LimitAngularVelocityModifier3D
Path: godot/classes/class_limitangularvelocitymodifier3d.rst
Summary: This modifier limits bone rotation angular velocity by comparing poses between previous and current frame.

This modifier limits bone rotation angular velocity by comparing poses between previous and current frame.

You can add bone chains by specifying their root and end bones, then add the bones between them to a list. Modifier processes either that list or the bones excluding those in the list depending on the option exclude.

Note: Most methods in this class take an index parameter. This parameter specifies which setting list entry to return if the IK has multiple entries (e.g. settings/index/root_bone_name).
---CHUNK---
Document: LimitAngularVelocityModifier3D
Path: godot/classes/class_limitangularvelocitymodifier3d.rst
Summary: Defines properties for modifying angular velocity limits in a 3D physics context.

Properties
* chain_count (int): The number of physics chains to affect. Default: 0
* exclude (bool): If true, the modifier will affect all chains except the specified ones. Default: false
* joint_count (int): The number of physics joints to affect. Default: 0
* max_angular_velocity (float): The maximum angular velocity allowed for the affected chains/joints. Default: 6.2831855
