Summary: This section details the methods available for managing bone chains within the LimitAngularVelocityModifier3D class, including setting, getting, and clearing bone indices and names, as well as resetting the reference pose.

Method: clear_chains() → void
Clear all bone chains.

Method: get_end_bone(index: int) → int
Returns the end bone index of the specified bone chain.

Method: get_end_bone_name(index: int) → String
Returns the end bone name of the specified bone chain.

Method: get_root_bone(index: int) → int
Returns the root bone index of the specified bone chain.

Method: get_root_bone_name(index: int) → String
Returns the root bone name of the specified bone chain.

Method: reset() → void
Sets the reference pose for angle comparison to the current pose with the influence of constraints removed. This function is automatically triggered when joints change or upon activation.

Method: set_end_bone(index: int, bone: int) → void
Sets the end bone index for the specified bone chain.

Method: set_end_bone_name(index: int, bone_name: String) → void
Sets the end bone name for the specified bone chain. Note: End bone must be the root bone or a child of the root bone.

Method: set_root_bone(index: int, bone: int) → void
Sets the root bone index for the specified bone chain.

Method: set_root_bone_name(index: int, bone_name: String) → void
Sets the root bone name for the specified bone chain.